<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy | Loop AI" %>

<section class="marketing-section">
  <div class="marketing-container marketing-legal">
    <p class="marketing-eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="marketing-section__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted mb-5">Last updated <%= Date.new(2026, 7, 23).strftime("%B %-d, %Y") %></p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">1. What this covers</h2>
    <p>
      This policy explains what Loop AI collects and why — both for workspace accounts (people
      who create and manage loops) and for respondents (people invited to a voice interview).
    </p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">2. Information we collect</h2>
    <p><strong>Workspace accounts:</strong> your name, email address, and password; anything you
    add for your organization, like a name, logo, or theme colors.</p>
    <p><strong>Respondents:</strong> the audio and transcript of your conversation with the voice
    agent, an AI-generated sentiment label and rationale, and — only if the workspace's invite
    link happens to include it — your email address. We don't otherwise ask respondents to sign
    in or identify themselves.</p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">3. How we use it</h2>
    <p>
      Transcripts are used to extract themes, feature requests, and sentiment for the workspace
      that ran the loop, so quotes are always traceable back to the exact conversation they came
      from. Account information is used to run the service itself (authentication, team invites,
      email notifications). We don't sell personal data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">4. Who else sees it</h2>
    <p>We share data with the following service providers, only as needed to run Loop AI:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>ElevenLabs</strong> — powers the voice conversation itself and produces the
      transcript and sentiment.</li>
      <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> — analyzes transcripts to extract themes and feature requests.</li>
      <li><strong>Amazon Web Services (S3)</strong> — stores uploaded files like organization logos.</li>
      <li><strong>Postmark</strong> — delivers transactional email (invites, notifications).</li>
      <li><strong>Heroku</strong> — hosts the application and database.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We don't share respondent data across workspaces — a loop's feedback is only visible to
    the workspace that created it.</p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">5. How long we keep it</h2>
    <p>
      We keep feedback and account data for as long as the workspace exists, so its owner can
      keep reviewing past interviews. Deleting a workspace or account removes its loops and
      feedback; deleted data isn't recoverable.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">6. Security</h2>
    <p>
      Data is scoped to the workspace it belongs to, transferred over HTTPS, and only accessible
      to signed-in members of that workspace.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">7. Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      Workspace members can update or delete their account, or delete the whole workspace, from
      Settings. If you're a respondent and want your conversation removed, contact the workspace
      that invited you, or reach us directly and we'll help.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">8. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We'll update the date at the top of this page whenever this policy changes.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h4 mt-5">9. Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy? Reach us at <a href="mailto:hi@getloop.me">hi@getloop.me</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>
